.SH NAME
ext2_discard_reservation \- 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ext2_discard_reservation
.BI "(struct inode *inode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "inode" 12
inode
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Discard(free) block reservation window on last file close, or truncate
or at last \fBiput\fP.

It is being called in three cases:
\fBext2_release_file\fP: last writer closes the file
\fBext2_clear_inode\fP: last \fBiput\fP, when nobody links to this file.
\fBext2_truncate\fP: when the block indirect map is about to change.
